introduction.p:
We denote each term by letter  U . The quantity  U  in each case is called  potential energy.
The potential energies for the four forces listed above have the following formulas.

	 \amp U_{\text{weight}} = mgy
	 \amp U_{\text{spring}} =\dfrac{1}{2}kx^2 
	 \amp U_{\text{gravitation}} = -\dfrac{Gm_1m_2}{r}   
	 \amp U_{\text{gravitation}} =  \dfrac{1}{4\pi\epsilon_0}\dfrac{q_1q_2}{r}
